# Privacy Policy

**Lafhane**  
Effective Date: February 23, 2026  

Lafhane is operated by **Mehmet Fatih Bayraktar**.

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the Lafhane mobile application and web application (the "Service").

---

## 1. Information We Collect

### 1.1 Information You Provide

We may collect the following information when you use the Service:

- Username
- Email address
- Authentication data (Google Sign-In, Apple Sign-In)
- In-game profile information
- Support communications

### 1.2 Automatically Collected Information

When you use the Service, we may automatically collect:

- Device type and operating system
- IP address
- Log files and error reports
- Gameplay statistics
- Session duration and usage data

### 1.3 Payment Information

If you purchase in-game credits, subscriptions, or other digital goods:

- Payments are processed by third-party providers such as Google Play or Apple App Store.
- We do not store credit card numbers or payment details.
- We only receive confirmation of successful transactions.

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

- Provide and maintain the Service
- Enable multiplayer gameplay
- Process transactions
- Improve performance and user experience
- Detect and prevent fraud or abuse
- Provide customer support
- Comply with legal obligations

---

## 3. Multiplayer and Public Information

Lafhane is a real-time online multiplayer game.

During gameplay:
- Your username
- Your in-game score
- Your ranking or match results

may be visible to other players.

---

## 4. Analytics and Monitoring

We may use monitoring and logging systems to:

- Diagnose technical issues
- Improve system stability
- Analyze performance

These systems may collect technical and diagnostic data.

---

## 5. Data Sharing

We do not sell personal information.

We may share data with:

- Cloud hosting providers
- Authentication providers (Google, Apple)
- Payment processors
- Legal authorities if required by law

---

## 6. Data Retention

We retain personal information:

- For as long as your account is active
- As required by applicable laws
- As necessary for legitimate business purposes

You may request deletion of your account and associated data.

---

## 7. Children's Privacy

The Service is not intended for children under 13 years of age.

We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.

If you believe that a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can remove the data.

---

## 8. Your Rights

Depending on your location (including Canada and the European Union), you may have rights to:

- Access your personal data
- Correct inaccurate information
- Request deletion of your data
- Object to certain processing
- Withdraw consent

To exercise your rights, contact us using the information below.

---

## 9. Data Security

We implement reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect your data. However, no internet transmission is completely secure.

---

## 10. International Data Transfers

Your information may be processed and stored in countries outside your country of residence.

By using the Service, you consent to such transfers.

---

## 11. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updated versions will be posted with a revised effective date.

---

## 12. Contact Information

For questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:

**Mehmet Fatih Bayraktar**  
Email: devtofro@gmail.com
